overallPriceChange:
(lastClose - firstOpen) / firstOpen * 100
What it measures:
The total percentage change from the first candle's open price to the last candle's close price across the entire analysis window
Shows the net movement over the complete period
Use case:
Best for understanding the "big picture" trend over the entire timeframe
Useful for identifying whether the overall movement was up/down regardless of volatility

avgPriceChange:
What it measures:
The average of percentage changes between consecutive closes
Shows the typical step-by-step movement
Use case:
Better for understanding the consistency/smoothness of the trend
Reveals whether price moved steadily or with high volatility


